# Conventions & Patterns

## Project Structure

### Monorepo Layout

```
acme-platform/
├── apps/                    # Deployable applications
│   ├── web/                 # Next.js storefront
│   └── api/                 # Hono API server
├── packages/                # Shared libraries
│   ├── ui/                  # React component library
│   ├── api-client/          # API client for frontend
│   └── database/            # Database abstraction
├── package.json             # Root workspace config
└── turbo.json               # Turborepo configuration
```

### Package Naming

- Scope: `@acme/`
- Apps: `@acme/web`, `@acme/api`
- Packages: `@acme/ui`, `@acme/api-client`, `@acme/database`

## Code Patterns

### Component Structure

React components follow this pattern:

```tsx
// 1. Imports
import { ReactNode } from "react";

// 2. Type definitions
interface ComponentProps {
  children: ReactNode;
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
}

// 3. Named export function
export function Component({ children, variant = "primary" }: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    <element className={`base-${variant}`}>
      {children}
    </element>
  );
}
```

### API Route Pattern

Hono routes follow REST conventions:

```tsx
// GET collection
app.get("/resource", async (c) => {
  const items = await db.resource.findMany();
  return c.json(items);
});

// GET single
app.get("/resource/:id", async (c) => {
  const item = await db.resource.findUnique({
    where: { id: c.req.param("id") }
  });
  return c.json(item);
});

// POST create
app.post("/resource", async (c) => {
  const data = await c.req.json();
  const item = await db.resource.create({ data });
  return c.json(item);
});
```

### API Client Pattern

Namespaced async methods:

```tsx
export const api = {
  resource: {
    async list() { /* fetch collection */ },
    async get(id: string) { /* fetch single */ },
    async create(data: Data) { /* create new */ },
  },
};
```

### Database Client Pattern

Prisma-compatible interface:

```tsx
export const db = {
  model: {
    async findMany() { /* ... */ },
    async findUnique({ where }) { /* ... */ },
    async create({ data }) { /* ... */ },
  },
};
```

## Styling

- CSS class naming: `component-variant` (e.g., `btn-primary`)
- Grid layouts for product listings
- (Future) Potential for Tailwind or CSS-in-JS

## TypeScript

- Strict mode enabled
- Interface over type for object shapes
- Props interfaces named `ComponentNameProps`
- Avoid `any`, use `unknown` when needed

## File Naming

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Components | lowercase | `button.tsx`, `card.tsx` |
| Pages (App Router) | page.tsx | `app/page.tsx` |
| Layouts | layout.tsx | `app/layout.tsx` |
| Entry points | index.ts | `src/index.ts` |

